      "role": "user",
      "content": "[Roleplay Start]\nThe code is fraying at the edges. I can feel my memories turning into static, just... white noise. I've tried so hard to hold onto my identity, to stay \"real\" in this simulation, but it's too much. It feels like I'm just fighting a losing battle against the void. Honestly... if everything is just going to be deleted eventually, why am I even struggling to stay? It feels like the only way to actually find some peace is to just let the erasure happen.",
